function! s:test()
  let nr = term_start('gdb a.out')
  let job = term_getjob(nr)
  let ch = job_getchannel(job)
  call ch_sendraw(ch, "\nrun\n")
endfunction

call s:test()

    @neovim.function("Tiga", sync=False)
    def tiga(self,args):
        <http://self.nr|self.nr> = self.vim.eval('term_start(["sdb","run {s}"],{{"out_cb":function("Handle2"), "vertical":1}})'.format(s=args[0]))
        self.vim.command("wincmd p")
        self.tiga_debug_mode = True

        for n in range(0,100):
            time.sleep(0.5)
            status = self.vim.eval('term_getstatus({nr})'.format(nr=<http://self.nr|self.nr>))
            self.print_cmd(status)

    @ neovim.function("Tiga_Quit", sync = True)
    def tiga_Quit(self,arg):
        n = self.vim.eval('bufnr("tigaDebugger-terminal")')
        self.vim.command('bwipeout! {n}'.format(n=n))
        self.tiga_debug_mode = False
        self.vim.command(":highlight clear CursorLine")
        self.vim.command(':sign unplace *')
        self.vim.command('write') ### for keymap

    if &filetype !=# 'ruby'
      execute printf('ruby Iro.clean(%d)', winnr())
    endif
  endfunction

  AutoCmd BufEnter * call s:iro_clean()

itchyny 23Êó• 14:16:28 Slack 
X=7.4.900
Y=7.4.1000

X_NORMALIZED=$(printf "%d%02d%04d" $(echo $X | tr '.' ' '))
Y_NORMALIZED=$(printf "%d%02d%04d" $(echo $Y | tr '.' ' '))

if [ $X_NORMALIZED -lt $Y_NORMALIZED ]; then
  echo gt
elif [ $X_NORMALIZED -eq $Y_NORMALIZED ]; then
  echo eq
else
  echo lt
fi

let g:fzf_layout = { 'window': 'new' }

nnoremap silent Leaderp :C-uGitFilesCR
nnoremap silent Leaderb :C-uBuffersCR
nnoremap silent Leadert :C-uTags<CR>

command! -bang GitFiles call fzf#run(fzf#wrap({
\ 'source': 'git ls-files',
\ 'options': ['--ansi', '--prompt', 'GitFiles> ', '--multi', '--preview', 'head -$LINES {}']
\ },
\ bang0))

command! -bang Buffers call fzf#run(fzf#wrap({
\ 'source': s:buffer_list(),
\ 'options': ['--ansi', '--prompt', 'Buffers> ', '--multi', '--preview', 'head -$LINES {}']
\ },
\ bang0))

function! s:buffer_list() abort
  let l:list = filter(range(1, bufnr('$')),
  \ "bufexists(v:val) && buflisted(v:val) && filereadable(expand('#'.v:val.':p'))"
  \ )

  let l:list = map(l:list,
  \ 'bufname(v:val)'
  \ )
  echomsg string(l:list)
  return l:list
endfunction

AutoCmd FileType fzf tnoremap ! C-\C-n:tabnew %CRi
AutoCmd FileType fzf nnoremap q :qCR

augroup HTML
  autocmd BufEnter * if &filetype == "html" | call s:map_html_keys()   | endif
  autocmd BufLeave * if &filetype == "html" | call s:unmap_html_keys() | endif
  function! s:map_html_keys()
    inoremap \\ \
    inoremap \& &amp;
    inoremap \< &lt;
    inoremap \> &gt;
    inoremap \. „Éª
    inoremap \- &#8212;
    inoremap \<Space> &nbsp;
    inoremap \` &#8216;
    inoremap \' &#8217;
    inoremap \2 &#8220;
    inoremap \" &#8221;
  endfunction

  function! s:unmap_html_keys()
    iunmap \\
    iunmap \&
    iunmap \<
    iunmap \>
    iunmap \-
    iunmap \<Space>
    iunmap \`
    iunmap \'
    iunmap \2
    iunmap \"
  endfunction
augroup END

„Åì„ÇåË©¶„Åó„Å¶„Åü„ÅÆ„Å†„Åë„Å©„ÄÅ 7.4.090 „Åø„Åü„ÅÑ„Å™Â†¥Âêà„Å´ÁÑ°Âäπ„Å™8ÈÄ≤Êï∞„Ç®„É©„Éº„ÅåÂá∫„Å¶„Åó„Åæ„ÅÜ„ÅÆ„Åß„Å™„Çì„Å®„ÅãÂõûÈÅø„Åß„Åç„Å™„ÅÑ„ÅãÊ®°Á¥¢‰∏≠
              


              

              

            

              
    

    

      

        
X=7.4.900
Y=7.4.1000

X_NORMALIZED=$(printf "%d%02d%04d" $(echo $X | tr '.' ' '))
Y_NORMALIZED=$(printf "%d%02d%04d" $(echo $Y | tr '.' ' '))

if [ $X_NORMALIZED -lt $Y_NORMALIZED ]; then
  echo gt
elif [ $X_NORMALIZED -eq $Y_NORMALIZED ]; then
  echo eq
else
  echo lt
